					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Registers the gift of a garden by purchase for 20 <hi rend="italic">poṉ (araimaṉai-mariyādi)</hi> as per the prevailing rates to Iḍavai Tiruvaraṅgadāsar by Sōmakkaṉ, son of Māchchavai, an attendant <hi rend="italic">(tādi)</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Sōmaladēviyār</hi> in order to serve the lord with garlands for his own merit and for the merit of his parents. The record is dated in the <hi rend="bold">29th (28+1) year</hi> of the king's reign.</p>						

						</summary>
